ces that won't resolve at runtime, and I need to verify what else is missing from the build configuration and main entry point.\n\nLooking at the package dependencies, video.js isn't listed, and the PlaybackView is trying to import it as a global without declaring it as a dependency. The web package is missing the Vue Router configuration that main.js claims to set up, so the router setup is incomplete or non-existent. VueRouter is referenced but not in package.json, and video.js has the same issue. Let me verify the build actually works.\n\nActually, I should just go through each problem systematically and fix them one by one.\n\nWait, I need to look at this more carefully. The issue description says to write the report framework first, then fix problems, so I always have output regardless of time. I already created the framework, so now I should be fixing issues rather than just listing them.\n\nLet me go through the critical issues and work through them.\n\nActually, rereading the instructions: I write the framework first, then in the loop I check each success criteria, fix problems directly with Edit or Bash, and update the report. So I should be making targeted edits, not just documenting issues. Let me start with the most impactful fixes.\n\nWait, I'm realizing something. The instructions say to use Edit or Bash to fix issues in the project files, not to fix the review report itself. The review report is my output, not something I should be editing.\n\nLet me look at the actual build.sh to understand the compilation process, then I'll identify which problems have the highest impact and fix them.","signature":"ef6c5c009ce4940362ae131e0df992829214e81273f38a1199270a5a3229639a"}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":45235,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":19028},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7030919-046f-4d40-9