a string. I need to either normalize the frontend to send JSON-encoded SessionDescription objects, or update the backend to handle both formats. Since I can't add gorilla/websocket without modifying the dependencies, the simpler fix is to correct the frontend message structure to match what the backend actually expects.\n\nThere's also a separate issue with how the backend processes the SDP value. When the backend does `SDP: string(msg.Payload)`, it's converting the raw JSON string directly into the SDP field, which would embed the JSON string itself rather than parsing it properly. The backend would then try to set a remote description with that JSON string as the SDP, which is malformed.\n\nBut wait—looking at the actual backend code more carefully, it unmarshals the payload into a webrtc.ICECandidateInit struct. If the frontend sends a raw JSON string instead of a structured object, the unmarshal would fail. So there are two distinct issues: the SDP is being sent as a raw string when it should be part of a SessionDescription object, and the ICE candidate handling might also be broken depending on what format the frontend is actually sending.\n\nThe frontend message format is inconsistent between the initial offer (sending just the SDP string) and subsequent ICE candidates (sending the full candidate object). I need to make the frontend send proper SessionDescription objects for offers/answers instead of raw strings.\n\nFor the backend, I'm constrained by Gin not having native WebSocket support, so I'll need to note that this requires either adding a WebSocket library or restructuring. Let me focus on fixing the frontend message format to match what the backend expects.","signature":"4477d5c7cb45669ecc451f4563db92e66de21a586beb4650b8cfede2cf743e58"}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":55592,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":19028},"service_tier":"standard","context_manage